  "text": "EPC proliferation was evaluated by bromo-deoxyuridine (BrdUrd) incorporation as described previously. [CITATION_1] Briefly, cells (2.5ϫ10 4 cells/well) were seeded on rat vitronectin (50 g/mL at 37°C for 1 hour) coated 4-well chamber slides and cultured in regular medium with glucose following 24 hour-serum starvation. After 18 hours in culture, BrdUrd (10 mol/L, Sigma) was added to each well and incubated with cells for 6 hours. BrdUrd was visualized by immunostaining with anti-BrdUrd antibody (1:100, Biodesign), and proliferation activity was expressed as averaged BrdUrd positive cell percentage in 5 high-power fields (ϫ40).",
